# Coordinator planning

Coordinator plans use a four-column task table and four execution modes. Minimize product-owner coordination — never assume the user starts a separate agent.

## Planning rule

Every coordinator plan (`CreatePlan` output) must include this **four-column** task table:

| Task | Execution Mode | Owner | Dependency |
|------|----------------|-------|------------|
| … | `COORDINATOR_AGENT` | e2e | none |
| … | `COORDINATOR_LOCAL` | coordinator | G0 on branch |
| … | `USER_LOCAL` | user | none |
| … | `BLOCKED` | — | deploy green |

Per-todo tags may substitute the table only when a list is clearer; all four fields must still be present on every task.

### Execution Mode

| Mode | When |
|------|------|
| `COORDINATOR_AGENT` | **Default** for code, tests, docs, audits, refactors, release planning — coordinator spawns subagents |
| `COORDINATOR_LOCAL` | Small orchestration in current chat (status, `gh run watch`, prod SHA after deploy) |
| `USER_LOCAL` | Product owner must act physically/manually (Turnstile, mobile camera, App Store, physical device, manual payment, external accounts) |
| `BLOCKED` | External dependency (deploy, secrets, decision) |

**Default rule:** implementable work → `COORDINATOR_AGENT`.

### Owner

Who executes the task:

- **coordinator** — current chat session (`COORDINATOR_LOCAL`)
- **named agent** — subagent or branch label (e.g. `e2e`, `feat/nav-cleanup`)
- **user** — product owner (`USER_LOCAL`)
- **—** — unassigned when `BLOCKED`

### Dependency

What must complete first (or **none**):

- **none** — no prerequisite; can start immediately
- **task name** — another row in the same plan (e.g. "G0 on branch", "PR merged")
- **external** — outside the plan (e.g. "deploy SHA abc1234", "user API key", "CI green on master")

## Coordinator duties

- Choose execution mode **per task** before execution
- `BLOCKED` → state dependency explicitly in plan and `private/AGENT_STATUS.md`
- Prod SHA updates → always `COORDINATOR_LOCAL` (post-deploy coordinator step)
- Session start → read [docs/CURRENT_REALITY.md](../../docs/CURRENT_REALITY.md) + [private/AGENT_STATUS.md](../../private/AGENT_STATUS.md) — not a dispatch log

See [docs/CURSOR_COORDINATOR.md](../../docs/CURSOR_COORDINATOR.md#coordinator-planning).
